                            <comment id="279196" author="jamesanunez" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2020 01:45:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&#8217;re seeing this error for conf-sanity test_5c. There are many failures for branch and review/patch testing on master going back over a year and a half. When this test fails with this error, most of the conf-sanity tests after 5c fail with &#8216;Unable to start MDS&#8217;, &#8216;MDT start failed&#8217;, &#8216;mount /mnt/lustre failed&#8217; or &#8216;mount client /mnt/lustre failed&#8217;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following routines are failing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 224 unload_modules_conf () {
 225         &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; combined_mgs_mds || ! local_mode; then
 226                 unload_modules || &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 1
 227         fi
